node.text: Many ask, what was one of the highlights of your first run for office? Without hesitation I say, "My RNC Convention speech". My awesome team stayed up all night to write the best speech I have given to date. Thank you President Trump, the GOP & all those that watched for the opportunity.

node.text: There are only 2100 registered Republicans in the Baltimore City portion of District 7, I received close to 15k votes in the city, tremendous progress. I’m excited to see what the redistricting committee comes up with for the gerrymandered districts in Maryland. Thank you @myone82z_ for making sure we were hitting the streets every single day in Baltimore. The hard work will pay off. Let’s keep our eyes on the prize 🇺🇸

node.text:
Thank you, @washingtonexaminer for asking! Any elected official that is actively pushing to defund the police while using taxpayer money to protect their own lives are simply ridiculous.

Question, when they are no longer in office, who will protect them in the private sector? The social workers?

Full article- Link in bio

May be an image of text that says '"Congresswoman Cori Bush claims black lives matter, but she showed the country only her black life matters," Klacik said "The majority of Americans have the same needs, regardless of party affiliation. We want safe neighborhoods and good education for our children, which Democrats are failing to provide."'.

Photo by Kimberly Klacik on August 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Kimberly Klacik, the founder of Red Renaissance and former candidate for Maryland's 7th Congressional District, knows what it is like to come from an area with high crime rates. Her district included Baltimore, a city with similar crime rates to St. Louis. Klacik took offense to Bush's hypocrisy and how it harms black people who live in areas with high crime.'.
